    <item>
      <title>Youth Reflection: Kids Help Phone AI Training Pilot</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/news/kids-help-phone-reflection-2026/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/news/kids-help-phone-reflection-2026/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Kids Help Phone youth councillor &lt;strong&gt;Simran&lt;/strong&gt; has written a reflection piece on RML&amp;rsquo;s recent pilot project conducted in partnership with &lt;a href=&#34;https://kidshelpphone.ca/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Kids Help Phone&lt;/a&gt; — exploring the development of an agentic AI framework for training frontline support workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The piece offers a youth perspective on how AI-assisted training tools could improve the consistency and quality of mental health support for young people. Read the full reflection: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.longwoods.com/content/27829/insights/one-session-infinite-support-a-youth-perspective-on-mental-health-research&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;One Session, Infinite Support: A Youth Perspective on Mental Health Research&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
